Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine red-brown. Circular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 122, 21. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0062.25. Name Apatourios.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1712)
